---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '../../components/Navigation.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <Navigation />
  <div class="project-detail-container">
    <a href="/projects" class="back-link">← Back to Projects</a>
    <header class="project-header">
      <h1>Target 0 Website</h1>
      <span class="category-badge">UX</span>      
    </header>

    <div class="project-image-large">
        <img src="/projects/target0.png" alt="Target 0 Website" />
    </div>

    <section class="project-section">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>UX and UI design for a website that promotes zero food waste practices by reducing waste and changing individual habits.</p>
	  <p>I conducted subject research, created user personas, mapped user journeys, and designed an engaging interface that would encourage sustainable food practices.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="project-section">
      <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
      <div class="tech-list">
        <span class="tech-item">Figma</span>
        <span class="tech-item">Personas</span>
        <span class="tech-item">User Journey Mapping</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="project-section">
        <h2>Design Process</h2>
        <section class="process-section">
            <h3>The Problem</h3>
			<p>For a UX class project, we were tasked with acting as a UX and UI consultant for a client who wanted to promote sustainable food practices. They wanted the website to feature <a href="https://www.bbcearth.com/news/7-day-no-food-waste-challenge">the BBC Earth 7-day no food waste challenge</a>.</p>
			<p>We received little guidance on the website requirements or user needs. To make the website engaging, we were tasked with adding unique features that would keep the user coming back.</p>
        </section>
	    <section class="process-section">
			<h3>Ideate</h3>
			<div class="process-flex">
				<div class="process-text">
					<p>I started by researching competing websites and identifying the target audience. </p>
					<p>In competing websites, I noticed they included statistics, had posts of information, and encouraged users to share the posts on social media.</p>
					<p>However, there seemed to be only a focus on the environment or sustainability conferences. The websites didn't focus on creating a community around the 7-day no food waste challenge or provide additional tips. There seemed to be a gap in addressing the social aspect of the challenge.</p>

				</div>
				<div class="process-image">
					<div id="slideshow-container" style="position:relative;">
						<img id="slideshow-img" src="/projects/persona1.png" alt="Persona for Target 0" style="width:100%; border-radius:16px; box-shadow:0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.13); object-fit:contain; max-width:700px; max-height:600px;" />
						<button id="prev-slide" class="carousel-button prev" >&#10094;</button>
						<button id="next-slide" class="carousel-button next" >&#10095;</button>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="process-below">
				<p>I identified the target audience to be environmentally conscious individuals and those who are lower income and want to reduce food waste to save money.</p>
				<p>With this understanding, I created two personas to guide the design process.</p>
				<p>To address the social aspect of the challenge, I decided to add a blog section for users to share tips and stories about each challenge as well as a knowledge base for Target 0 to provide educational resources.</p>
				<p>To encourage engagement, within the home page, users would be encouraged to participate in the challenge and explore the blog and knowledge base.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="figma-container">
				<h4>Wireframing</h4>
				<p>I took the website through low and high fidelity wireframes, focusing on the layout and user flow.</p>
				<iframe style="border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);" width="800" height="300" src="https://embed.figma.com/design/JgzxfNvXARm4uApPKlTojJ/Midterm-UX?node-id=0-1&embed-host=share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
			</div>
		</section>
		<br>
        <section class="process-section">
            <h3>Prototype</h3>
            <p>After finalizing the wireframes, I created a high-fidelity prototype in Figma. </p>
			<p>The prototype included a home page, blog section, knowledge base, about page, and an explanation of the 7-day challenge, as well as a navigation bar and footer for easy access to different sections of the website.</p>
			<p>Lorem ipsum text was used for placeholder content.</p>
		</section>
        
    </section>
      

    <section class="project-section">
      <h2>View Project</h2>
      <a class="button-primary" href="https://www.figma.com/proto/uAypVZmtgV5fjzgOAgH9BL/Midterm-Prototype?node-id=71-11&t=z3auueZ1UuWzAwdQ-1&scaling=scale-down-width&content-scaling=fixed" target="_blank">Open Prototype in Figma</a>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
.project-detail-container {
		max-width: 900px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 40px 20px;
		font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
	}

	.back-link {
		display: inline-block;
		color: var(--color-dark);
		text-decoration: none;
		margin-bottom: 30px
		font-weight: 500;
		transition: color 0.2s;
		text-decoration: underline;
	}

	.back-link:hover {
		color: var(--color-secondary);
	}

	.project-header {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: center;
		margin-bottom: 30px;
		border-bottom: 2px solid #e5e7eb;
		padding-bottom: 20px;
	}

	.project-header h1 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 2.5em;
		color: #1f2937;
	}

	.category-badge {
		display: inline-block;
		background-color: var(--color-light);
		color: var(--text-color);
		padding: 8px 16px;
		border-radius: 20px;
		font-size: 0.9em;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.project-video {
		width: 100%;
		height: 0;
		padding-bottom: 56.25%;
		position: relative;
		margin-bottom: 40px;
		border-radius: 8px;
		overflow: hidden;
		background-color: #000;
	}

	.project-video iframe {
		position: absolute;
		top: 0;
		left: 0;
		width: 100%;
		height: 100%;
		border: 0;
	}

	.project-content {
		font-size: 1.05em;
		line-height: 1.8;
	}

	.project-section {
		margin-bottom: 40px;
	}

	.project-section h2 {
		font-size: 1.5em;
		margin-bottom: 15px;
		border-bottom: 1px solid #d1d5db;
		padding-bottom: 10px;
	}

	.project-section p {
		margin: 0 0 15px 0;
	}

	.tech-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.tech-item {
		display: inline-block;
		background-color: var(--color-light);
		color: var(--text-color);
		padding: 8px 16px;
		border-radius: 6px;
		font-weight: 500;
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.button {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 12px 24px;
		text-decoration: none;
		border-radius: 6px;
		transition: background-color 0.2s;
		border: none;
		cursor: pointer;
		font-size: 1em;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.button:hover {
		background-color: var(--color-primary-hover);
	}
    
    .ul .li{
        padding-left: 50px;
    }

    .process-section {
        margin-bottom: 60px;
    }
    
    .process-flex {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 32px;
		align-items: flex-start;
	}
	.process-text {
		flex: 1 1 320px;
		min-width: 0;
	}
	.process-image {
		flex: 1 1 400px;
		min-width: 320px;
		max-width: 700px;
		align-self: center;
	}
	.process-image img {
		width: 100%;
		height: auto;
		max-width: 700px;
		max-height: 600px;
		border-radius: 16px;
		box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.13);
		object-fit: contain;
	}

	ol, ul {
        margin-bottom: 18px;
		margin-top: 8px;
        padding-left: 30px !important;
    }

	li {
		margin-bottom: 10px;
		padding-left: 4px;
	}

	@media (min-width: 900px) {
		.process-flex {
			flex-direction: row;
			align-items: flex-start;
			gap: 48px;
		}
		.process-text, .process-image {
			max-width: 50%;
		}
		.process-image {
			align-self: flex-start;
		}
        #big-img {
            width: 120%;
        }
	}

    .project-image-large {
		width: 100%;
		margin-bottom: 40px;
		border-radius: 8px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.project-image-large img {
		width: 90%;
		height: auto;
		display: block;
        margin: auto;
	}

	.carousel-button {
		position: absolute;
		top: 50%;
		transform: translateY(-50%);
		background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
		color: white;
		border: none;
		font-size: 1.2em;
		padding: 10px;
		cursor: pointer;
		border-radius: 2px;
		transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
		z-index: 10;
	}

	.carousel-button:hover {
		background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
	}

	.carousel-button.prev {
		left: -35px;
	}

	.carousel-button.next {
		right: -35px;
	}

	.figma-container {
	width: 100%;
	height: 800px;
	margin-bottom: 80px;
	}

	.figma-container iframe {
	width: 100%;
	height: 100%;
	border: none;
	}
    

</style>

<script>
  const images = [
    '/projects/persona1.png',
    '/projects/persona2.png'
  ];
  let current = 0;
  window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const imgEl = document.getElementById('slideshow-img');
    const prevBtn = document.getElementById('prev-slide');
    const nextBtn = document.getElementById('next-slide');
    if (imgEl && prevBtn && nextBtn) {
      prevBtn.onclick = () => {
        current = (current - 1 + images.length) % images.length;
        imgEl.src = images[current];
      };
      nextBtn.onclick = () => {
        current = (current + 1) % images.length;
        imgEl.src = images[current];
      };
    }
  });
</script>